private sector business have been finding it harder to recruit , reported sean farrington on wake up to money on bbc radio 5 live .
the availability of permanent and temporary workers fell quite sharply in july as demand from businesses rose faster than the number of available candidates , according to the recruitment and employment confederation .
starting salaries are rising , but we 're not seeing that filterning through to everyone , he pointed out .
vicky pryce , economist with the centre for economics and business research said : `` people are staying in their jobs for longer than they used to with the result that firms feel they can get away with not paying their workers more . ''
